Key Match Events: Azzedine Ounahi scored the opening goal just eight minutes into the match.
Chadi Riad capitalized on another defensive error to score the second goal by the 16th minute.
Ayoub El Kaabi scored his first goal of the evening and Morocco’s third in the 16th minute, assisted by Achraf Hakimi.
El Kaabi scored his second goal in the 39th minute, assisted by Ounahi.
El Kaabi completed his hat-trick with a stunning header in the 53rd minute, assisted by Ounahi.
Soufiane Rahimi scored the sixth goal of the night in the 62nd minute, assisted by Brahim.
Post-Match Reflections: Achraf Hakimi and other key players were reliable and almost spectacular tonight.
Ayoub El Kaabi stood out as the player of the match with three goals and an assist.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Congo’s defense seemed unable to cope with Morocco’s relentless attack, resulting in three yellow cards.
Despite making two substitutions in an attempt to bolster their defense, Congo’s efforts were in vain.
The Congolese defense was left in shambles for the remainder of the game.
